dy></p:sp><p:sp><p:nvSpPr><p:cNvPr id="4" name="TextBox 3"/><p:cNvSpPr txBox="1"/><p:nvPr/></p:nvSpPr><p:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="868680" y="2240284"/><a:ext cx="10424160" cy="3447098"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"><a:avLst/></a:prstGeom><a:noFill/></p:spPr><p:txBody><a:bodyPr wrap="square"><a:spAutoFit/></a:bodyPr><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:pPr><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="800"/></a:spcAft></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr sz="2200" dirty="0"><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="1F2937"/></a:solidFill><a:latin typeface="Arial"/></a:rPr><a:t>RhythmRing is a community web platform where users create music together by recording tiny sound snippets using their voice, body sounds, nearby objects, or real instruments.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="800"/></a:spcAft></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr sz="2200" dirty="0"><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="1F2937"/></a:solidFill><a:latin typeface="Arial"/></a:rPr><a:t>Each sound clip is uploaded to the cloud and analyzed by Gemini to identify its possible role such as beat, melody, texture, or accent.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="800"/></a:spcAft></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr sz="2200" dirty="0"><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="1F2937"/></a:solidFill><a:latin typeface="Arial"/></a:rPr><a:t>The platform then helps members of a “ring” discover compatible clips and combine them into a collaborative track without needing formal music training.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="800"/></a:spcAft></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr sz="2200" dirty="0"><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="1F2937"/></a:solidFill><a:latin typeface="Arial"/></a:rPr><a:t>This lowers the barrier to music creation and turns it into a simple, social, and inclusive activity.</a:t></a:r></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp><p:pic><p:nvPicPr><p:cNvPr id="5" name="Google Shape;116;p27" title="frameeeee.png"><a:extLst><a:ext uri="{FF2B5EF4-FFF2-40B4-BE49-F238E27FC236}"><a16:creationId xmlns:a16="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2014/main" id="{23B3E03F-7314-8F94-FBB8-45149C99C4BA}"/